  <description type="morphology">Shrubs 1–3 m.  Stems erect or arching, forming clumps by underground runners, glabrous or sparsely pubescent.  Leaves: petiole 3–10 mm; blade elliptic to oblong-oblanceolate, 2–9 × 1–4 cm, margins glandular-serrate to serrulate or minutely denticulate.  Racemes arching, 20–80-flowered, 4–15 cm, rachis puberulent.  Pedicels 1–3.5 mm, puberulent.  Flowers: sepals erect or slightly divergent, narrowly oblong, 0.6–1 mm, apex acute; petals narrowly oblong, 3.5–6 mm; filaments 1–2 mm, pubescent; styles longitudinally grooved.  Capsules ± reflexed, cylindric, 0.7–1 cm, styles persistent, pubescent.  Seeds 1–1.4 × 0.4–0.9 mm, smooth, shiny.  2n = 22.</description>
